x
(20 + x) / (100 + x + y) = 0.3
y
(5 + y) / (100 + x + y) = 0.1
75 / (100 + x + y) = 0.6
20 + x = 0.3 (100 + x + y)
20 + x = 30 + 0.3x + 0.3y
-10 = -0.7x + 0.3y
5 + y = 0.1 (100 + x + y)
5 + y = 10 + 0.1x + 0.1y
-5 = 0.1x - 0.9y
\pmatrix{ -10 \\ -5 } = \pmatrix{ -0.7 & 0.3 \\ 0.1 & -0.9} \pmatrix { x \\ y }
\pmatrix{x \\ y } = \pmatrix{ 17.5 \\ 7.5 }
